  <span id="freeText5414872541893703245" style="display:none">How do you rate a book full of such honesty, tragedy, courage, hope, and every other emotion with a certain number of stars...it just seemms horribly inept. I will however rate this book based upon the emotional impact that it had on me and that was huge. <br /><br />My mom's mother died of cancer when my mom was just six (and she lost her dad just a few years later) and knowing what it was like for her made me think of the road that Mr. Beaver's little girl Maddie will have to face. It will not be easy for but luckily she has a very strong dad to help her and hold her hand along the way. <br /><br />Jim Beaver shares with the reader his love, frustrations, insecurities and imperfections. I applaud him for sharing his journal and may Cecily rest in peace knowing how much she was loved by her husband and her daughter. </span>
