              <span id="reviewTextContainer1028096808" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12708728830063882629">Read this in one sitting, now feel so emotionally wrung out. It might sound wrong to say I enjoyed this book due to the content, but this book left me ultimately full of hope, Hope for Jim and his beautiful sounding daughter, for the life they will forge together after their loss. The loss of Cec seems to have left a huge hole and one Jim is free to admit affects him when he least expects it, but one he is aware of, which to me sounds healthy, I expected this book to be a &apos;life is unfair&apos; and a </span>
  <span id="freeText12708728830063882629" style="display:none">Read this in one sitting, now feel so emotionally wrung out. It might sound wrong to say I enjoyed this book due to the content, but this book left me ultimately full of hope, Hope for Jim and his beautiful sounding daughter, for the life they will forge together after their loss. The loss of Cec seems to have left a huge hole and one Jim is free to admit affects him when he least expects it, but one he is aware of, which to me sounds healthy, I expected this book to be a 'life is unfair' and a ranting 'how hard done were we' but it has been written so honestly that you realise that although these statements are true he is very much aware how many people go through this every day. It takes a brave person to be so honest and put it out there for all to see and for that I thank you Jim Beaver and Maddie x </span>
