              <span id="reviewTextContainer1264704650" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13828423910450887881">Wow. Just wow. This book was beautiful and honest. It was loaned to me a couple of years ago when my mother passed away by a thoughtful friend that told me she believed it might be good for me to read. While I have to say that I&apos;m glad I waited this long to read it, I&apos;m so unbelievably happy that I did read it. While the relationship of the loss was different (Mr. Beaver and his wife, me and my mom), some of the emotion and thoughts and guilt and joy was all the same. Nobody grieves the same way</span>
  <span id="freeText13828423910450887881" style="display:none">Wow. Just wow. This book was beautiful and honest. It was loaned to me a couple of years ago when my mother passed away by a thoughtful friend that told me she believed it might be good for me to read. While I have to say that I'm glad I waited this long to read it, I'm so unbelievably happy that I did read it. While the relationship of the loss was different (Mr. Beaver and his wife, me and my mom), some of the emotion and thoughts and guilt and joy was all the same. Nobody grieves the same way, but it was nice to know that I wasn't the only person out there that had some of the thoughts like Mr. Beaver had go through my head. A wonderful memoir that I highly recommend to anyone who's lost someone they loved.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13828423910450887881" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

