              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5372197-megan?shelf=march-2019">march-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2724807491" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3202050252384365681">When I came across this book at the library and noticed it was written by Jim Beaver, whom I recognized from Supernatural, I knew I had to read it. <br/><br/>The book covers a year of emails Jim sent updating family and friends on his wife&apos;s cancer as well as other things going on. <br/><br/>It was moving reading it chronologically, as though going through it with them and there were plenty of ups and downs. <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[I was personally surprised how suddenly Cecily died. I know cancer can be very aggressive but</span></span>
  <span id="freeText3202050252384365681" style="display:none">When I came across this book at the library and noticed it was written by Jim Beaver, whom I recognized from Supernatural, I knew I had to read it. <br /><br />The book covers a year of emails Jim sent updating family and friends on his wife's cancer as well as other things going on. <br /><br />It was moving reading it chronologically, as though going through it with them and there were plenty of ups and downs. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I was personally surprised how suddenly Cecily died. I know cancer can be very aggressive but I just wasn't expecting it so soon. I also had no idea beforehand that his wife had died so I went into this unknowing of the outcome, which made it all the more shocking.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />I think if you're someone who enjoys reading memoirs like this you sound give this a read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3202050252384365681" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


