              <span id="reviewTextContainer2685629245" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8291624192051400140">Wow! Tore my heart apart yet made me laugh through some of my tears. So inspirational and insightful . A must read for anyone grieving a loss and learning to move on .<br/>I had the privilege to listen to the audiobook read by the author . Even though I know Mr. Beaver best as Bobby on Supernatural, this book allowed me a chance to see him as a husband , a father and a human being . There&apos;s so much more him than the characters he plays . Thank you Jim, for opening your heart. I will never forget this</span>
  <span id="freeText8291624192051400140" style="display:none">Wow! Tore my heart apart yet made me laugh through some of my tears. So inspirational and insightful . A must read for anyone grieving a loss and learning to move on .<br />I had the privilege to listen to the audiobook read by the author . Even though I know Mr. Beaver best as Bobby on Supernatural, this book allowed me a chance to see him as a husband , a father and a human being . There's so much more him than the characters he plays . Thank you Jim, for opening your heart. I will never forget this story . Cecilia is surely proud of both you and Maddie . I will always remember to hum along .</span>
